1:# Rhei States Specification
12:- Per-state `all_models: [<model-id>, ...]` to declare the full model set that may execute that state
15:- Per-state `agent_timeout: <duration>` to set the maximum time an agent may work in this state
17:- Per-state `program_timeout: <duration>` to set the maximum time a program may run in this state
19:- Per-state `inputs:` / `outputs:` artifact contracts to require workspace files on entry/exit; individual inputs may be marked `optional: true` to skip the existence check while still exposing the path and an existence flag to agents and programs
20:- Per-state `mcp_servers:` and `skills:` lists to attach MCP servers and agent skills to the agent subprocess for that state; individual entries may be marked `optional: true` to warn-and-continue rather than block when the tool is unavailable
27:both forms and may be combined with either single-target or fanout execution.
53:## Schema Additions
